  "prompt": "What are the legal precedents related to money laundering cases?",
  "response": "There are many legal precedents related to money laundering cases. Some key cases include:\n\n1. United States v. Bajakajian (1998)\n- Supreme Court case about civil asset forfeiture\n- Limited government's ability to seize money\n\n2. Bank of Credit and Commerce International (BCCI) case\n- Major international money laundering investigation\n- Led to significant regulatory reforms\n\n3. United States v. Merchant (2009)\n- Established guidelines for prosecuting complex money laundering schemes\n\n4. United States v. Santos (2008)\n- Clarified legal definition of money laundering activities\n\n5. Proceeds of Crime Act (UK, 2002)\n- Landmark legislation expanding money laundering prevention\n\nThese cases have shaped legal approaches to investigating and prosecuting money laundering. However, for specific legal advice, I recommend consulting a qualified attorney who can provide professional guidance.\n\nWould you like me to explain any of these cases in more detail?",
